I was figuring, whicever pet that isn't for sale off vendors are probably to better pets per spell circle. Am I right??<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 209<br> <font color=#333333>(12/20/02 5:19:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Which one??</span><hr size=1> It really depends on your playstyle and the mobs you're fighting.  I solo a lot, so my needs were from that perspective.<br>
<br>
From 1-34, I probably used water more than any other pet.  Once I hit 34, fire became my primary choice until 51, where earth became my primary pet.  At 53, I went with air until 57.  At 57, I started using earth again, and I've essentially stuck with it for soloing.<br>
<br>
However, I soloed a lot, and having fire tank with its awesome DS made a huge amount of sense for me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dabrighter2>Dabrighter2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(12/20/02 7:29:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Which one??</span><hr size=1> The style of Soloing will change which pet you use.  <br>
<br>
For me when soloing, a dead pet =&gt; dead mage.  I always tried to keep my pet alive.  I would summon armor, shield, weapons, the focus items to help keep my pet alive. <br>
<br>
I always wanted the pet that could survive the longest with two or mobs beating on it.  {Any pet could take on one mob, but sometimes you would have an unexpected add, or could not seperate the mobs.}  <br>
<br>
Before 34th level, the fully buffed water pet could survive the longest.  At 34th, a fully buffed Air pet and a fully buffed water pet are about equal tanks, but I went with water because of the larger damage.  At 39th level, the Air pet is a noticably better tank.<br>
<br>
If you like to chain cast pets {This method is tons easier than it used to be.  Pet get lost is now a button on the interface and it is zone wide.  You only have to do 1 point of damage to it to get full XP.} Either Earth Pet + Damage Shield or just Fire Pet.  The Earth pet has more hit points and is hit a lot easier which results in more times the DS comes into effect.   Plus the Earth pet roots.  The Fire pet shields itself with a larger Damage Shield but does not have the HP of the Earth Pet.  I tended to use the Fire pet with the fastest damage spell (Burn) cast just before I though the Mob was going to die.  I did it this way mostly because it was one less spell to deal which made this technique easier to use.  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khalendor>Khalendor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#333333>(12/20/02 7:35:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Which one??</span><hr size=1> Leveling a mage at those levels for many of us was somewhat different than it is now since we had to out-damage our pets back then for more experience (unfortunately, I didn't chain cast until much much later).  That being said, I agree that pre-34 the water pet seemed like the pet of choice.  Actually, I think I continued to use the water pet even at level 39 since it seemed to have insane regen at that level. <p>Khalendor Dayze</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showPrevMessage?topicID=891.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showNextMessage?topicID=891.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.threadControl?topicID=891.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=h